         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve"><head>Translation</head>
            <div type="translation" resp="#edd" xml:lang="en"><p><ref target="https://godot.date/id/mDha8ivFFUEeijcoAswNPW">Year 9</ref>: Epagathos 
               <supplied reason="subaudible">son</supplied> of Herakleidas, three times an ephebe.</p></div></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>Another description of someone three times an ephebe is apparently recorded at <ref type="inscription" n="T.724">T.724</ref>; 
               for "twice an ephebe" see <ref type="inscription" n="P.402">P.402</ref> and <ref type="inscription" n="T.74">T.74</ref>  
               perhaps <ref type="inscription" n="T.45">T.45.i</ref>. 
               <!-- The normal duration of ephebic training seems to be 2 years, but there is evidence, e.g. from Chios, 
               to suggest that it might last longer (PW s.v. 'Eφηβία col. 2744). --> The impression given here is that Epagathos was exceptional. </p>
         </div>
         
